<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/49297068-kendall"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1519847457i/49297068._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/49297068-kendall">Kendall</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes and no. There are many parts in Losing Hope that are just from Holder&apos;s perspective from Hopeless. The story starts about a year before he meets S<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes and no. There are many parts in Losing Hope that are just from Holder's perspective from Hopeless. The story starts about a year before he meets Sky and there are some extra scenes as well. I was a little worried about reading it at first because I didn't want to reread the situations, but reading it in Holder's perspective just showed how great he really was. Hope this helps! <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
